    "## Evaluating data sources\n",
    "Drill - find possible shortcomings of the theoretical or actual data sources to answer the given question. \n",
    "What could be done to either adjust the analysis or reframe the question so that you can answer it accurately?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "1 Data Source - Amsterdam availability data scraped from Airbnb on December 24th. \n",
    "Question: What are the popular neighborhoods in Amsterdam?\n",
    "\n",
    "The shortcoming here is Amsterdam availability's data is biased by the behavior of people who use Airbnb. It also\n",
    "skewed based on the exceptional circumstance of being collected near Christmas. \n",
    "You could adjust and limit your conclusion to finding the popular Amsterdam neighborhoods on Airbnb.\n",
    "\n",
    "2 Data Source - Mental health services use on September 12, 2001 in San Francisco, CA and New York City, NY. \n",
    "Question: How do patterns of mental health service use vary between cities?\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "The shortcoming is the exceptional circumstance of being collected so near a national tragedy. The bias is that comparing New York City at one of the sights of the tragedy to other cities.\n",
    "\n",
    "3 Data Source: Armenian Pub Survey. \n",
    "Question: What are the most common reasons Armenians visit local pubs?\n",
    "\n",
    "People who take the survey will most likely be intoxicated.\t\n",
    " "
   ]
